---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Talks & Media" sideBarActiveItemID="talks">

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Talks & Media</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-8 text-lg opacity-80 italic">
    A selected set of talks, interviews, and lectures — organized by what they're about, not when they happened.
  </div>

  {/* INTRO VIDEO — placeholder; do not auto-fill */}
  <div class="aspect-video border border-base-300 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center bg-base-200 mb-12">
    <div class="text-center px-6">
      <div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider opacity-60 mb-2">Intro</div>
      <div class="text-base opacity-50 italic">60-second on-camera intro to be added</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* ===========================================================
      RESEARCH FINDINGS
      =========================================================== */}
  <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mt-12 mb-2">Research findings</div>
  <div class="mb-8 text-base opacity-70 italic">
    How institutional environments shape who becomes an entrepreneur and which ventures scale.
  </div>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Through the Mud or in the Boardroom</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      Conversation with Kelly DeCelles on activist tactics and how firms get targeted for social change. <em>Strategic Management Journal</em>, 2016 (with DeCelles and Lenox).
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/dtt1n9_9Lso"
        title="Through the Mud or in the Boardroom — research conversation"
        class="w-full h-full"
        allow="accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
        referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/smj.2458" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Read the paper ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Born into Chaos</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      How founding conditions shape whether ventures survive or thrive through environmental change. <em>Strategic Entrepreneurship Journal</em>, 2023 (with Motley and Koo).
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/4S30_WHgTi8"
        title="Born into Chaos — research conversation"
        class="w-full h-full"
        allow="accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
        referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/sej.1461" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Read the paper ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Entrepreneurial Strategies During Institutional Changes</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      What China's regional economic transition tells us about which entrepreneurial strategies pay off when institutions shift. <em>Strategic Entrepreneurship Journal</em>, 2022 (with Wu and Yang).
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/NXQUYyQdY1U"
        title="Entrepreneurial Strategies During Institutional Changes — research conversation"
        class="w-full h-full"
        allow="accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
        referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/sej.1399" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Read the paper ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Stanford Innovation Study: The Economic Impact of Stanford Entrepreneurship</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      Findings from the alumni survey with Bill Miller on the economic impact of Stanford-founded companies. Stanford eCorner, 2012.
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/414063301"
        title="Stanford Innovation Study — economic impact of Stanford entrepreneurship"
        class="w-full h-full"
        allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <a href="https://ecorner.stanford.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Alternate source: Stanford eCorner ↗</a>
  </article>

  {/* ===========================================================
      TEACHING & FRAMEWORKS
      =========================================================== */}
  <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mt-16 mb-2">Teaching & frameworks</div>
  <div class="mb-8 text-base opacity-70 italic">
    Ideas from the classroom — MS&E 272, ETL, and international programs.
  </div>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Technology Entrepreneurship — Stanford E145 / MS&E 178</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      Course preview for the flagship Stanford technology entrepreneurship course Chuck has taught since 2009 (cross-listed as Stanford Engineering 145 undergraduate and MS&E 178 graduate). Through the MOOC version, the course has reached more than 200,000 students globally.
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/115996333"
        title="Technology Entrepreneurship — Stanford Engineering 145 / MS&E 178 course preview"
        class="w-full h-full"
        allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLF6C0319C607DEDC1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Watch the full 27-lecture course on YouTube ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">The Future of Entrepreneurship Education at STVP</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      MS&E 25th Anniversary, May 2025. Opening vision for STVP and closing reflections, bookending a fireside chat between Steve Blank and Riitta Katila.
    </p>
    <div class="aspect-video mb-3 border border-base-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/aBjtSBEzgqU"
        title="The Future of Entrepreneurship Education at STVP — MS&E 25th Anniversary"
        class="w-full h-full"
        allow="accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
        referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <ul class="text-sm opacity-70 mt-3 ml-4 list-none">
      <li class="my-1"><span class="font-mono">0:00</span> &nbsp;— Opening vision (Chuck Eesley)</li>
      <li class="my-1"><span class="font-mono">9:59</span> &nbsp;— Fireside: Steve Blank with Riitta Katila</li>
      <li class="my-1"><span class="font-mono">45:06</span> — Closing on the future of STVP and MS&E (Chuck Eesley)</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Research Insight: Entrepreneurship Education Is About More than Startup Creation</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      ETL podcast, September 2021. How entrepreneurship education affects students who never found a startup.
    </p>
    <a href="https://stvp.stanford.edu/av/research-insight-entrepreneurship-education-about-more-startup-creation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Listen on STVP ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">It Takes an Ecosystem</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      eCorner collection on the environmental forces that shape startup ecosystems.
    </p>
    <a href="https://ecorner.stanford.edu/collection/chuck-eesleys-fully-charged-playlist-startups/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Browse the collection on eCorner ↗</a>
  </article>

  {/* ===========================================================
      CONVERSATIONS & INTERVIEWS
      =========================================================== */}
  <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mt-16 mb-2">Conversations & interviews</div>
  <div class="mb-8 text-base opacity-70 italic">
    Long-form discussions on research, career, and the institutional view of entrepreneurship.
  </div>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">"Stanford's Startup Prof"</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      Angel Invest Boston with Sal Daher, Episode 82. On the MIT / Ed Roberts lineage, NovoEd, and what makes ecosystems work.
    </p>
    <a href="https://www.angelinvestboston.com/ep-82-chuck-eesley/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Listen on Angel Invest Boston ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Mezcal Negronis and the Economics of Misinformation</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      Creative Distillation podcast (Episode 78), CU Boulder Leeds School of Business, March 2025. Conversation with Rob Hahn (founder of Avanti) on the algorithmic financing of online misinformation, AI-era venture diligence, and what the institutional environment around founders actually shapes.
    </p>
    <a href="https://www.colorado.edu/business/deming/news/2025/03/18/creative-distillation-episode-78-rob-hahn-founder-avanti-and-chuck-eesley" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Listen on Creative Distillation ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Innovating for Social Impact</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      ETL, April 2022. Conversation with Irma Olguin Jr. and Morgan Simon on high-growth startups and impact investors. Podcast and full-talk video.
    </p>
    <a href="https://stvp.stanford.edu/av/innovating-social-impact" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Watch / listen on STVP ↗</a>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">A Lens of Racial Equity</h3>
    <p class="text-base mb-4">
      ETL micro-episode, December 2020. Reflections on entrepreneurs' responsibility to build a more inclusive tech ecosystem.
    </p>
    <a href="https://stvp.stanford.edu/podcasts/2020-insight-a-lens-of-racial-equity/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link text-sm">Listen on STVP ↗</a>
  </article>

  {/* ===========================================================
      FOOTER NOTE
      =========================================================== */}
  <div class="border-t border-base-300 mt-16 pt-6 text-sm opacity-70 italic">
    For media inquiries or speaking requests, see the <a href="/contact" class="link">contact page</a>.
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
